# Project Info

## Domain
- Production domain: `flowone.pro`
- Never ask for the domain. It is `flowone.pro`.

## Server Stack
- Web server: OpenLiteSpeed
- PHP: 8.3 (lsphp83 at `/usr/local/lsws/lsphp83/bin/php`)
- Database: MariaDB
- Mail: Dovecot + Postfix
- Security: Fail2Ban, ModSec, CPGuard, FirewallD
- Cache: Redis
- Search: Meilisearch

## Paths on Server
- Email backend: `/var/www/vps-email/backend/`
- Email frontend: `/var/www/vps-email/frontend/`
- PHP error logs: `/var/www/vps-email/backend/logs/php_errors.log`
- Drive storage (local): `/var/www/vps-email/storage/drive/`
- Mood board cache: `/var/www/vps-email/storage/mood-uploads/`
- NAS mount: `/mnt/nas-drive` (NFS via OpenVPN to Synology at `192.168.1.106`)
- Backups NAS mount: `/mnt/vps-backup`

## NAS / VPN
- Synology NAS accessed via OpenVPN tunnel (`openvpn-client@synology`)
- Synology DDNS: `pixelranger.synology.me` (port 1194, public IP resolved dynamically)
- NFS mount options: `rw,soft,timeo=10,retrans=3,_netdev,nofail,x-systemd.automount`
- NAS healthcheck file: `/mnt/nas-drive/.healthcheck`
- NasHealthCheck PHP class guards all NAS filesystem access

## Deployment
- Code lives locally on Windows, uploaded to server manually
- No automated CI/CD pipeline
